      "content": "i guess, but it's hard to see it as just a \"struggle\" when one side's version seems to be about facts and the other is about making kids feel guilty or and focusing on identity politics. doesn't the move toward \"social justice issues\" in curriculum inherently mean the schools are taking a side instead of being objective?",
